{"status":200,"metadata":{"name":"AutoGen-model","type":"ai_tool.AutoGen-model","run_id":"debug","workflow_name":"pipeline-generator","workflow_type":"NodeType : ai-tool","workflow_id":"7c8b6522-e967-42d5-a116-85a83946640b","workflow_run_id":"0dbd8ec0-65c7-41e9-8440-941412cc7e36"},"data":{"Answer":"Node Explanation:\n\n*   **Image Reader:** This node is responsible for ingesting the raw image data. It assumes that the images are stored in a standard format (e.g., JPEG, PNG) and are accessible through a file path or directory.\n*   **Text Cleaner:** This node is included to handle any textual metadata associated with the images (e.g., patient ID, date of capture). Cleaning this metadata can improve the quality of any subsequent feature engineering steps.\n*   **Tokenizer:** Tokenizes the image metadata (if available) for potential feature engineering.\n*   **Skin Cancer Detection:** This node represents the core machine learning model. It leverages a CNN architecture, which is well-suited for image analysis tasks. Fine-tuning a pre-trained model on a skin cancer dataset allows for efficient learning and improved performance. The assumption here is that a labeled dataset of dermoscopic images is available for training.\n*   **Confusion Matrix Calculator:** This node calculates the confusion matrix, providing a detailed breakdown of the model's classification performance. It helps identify areas where the model may be struggling (e.g., misclassifying benign lesions as cancerous).\n*   **ROC Curve:** This node generates an ROC curve, which visually represents the model's ability to discriminate between cancerous and non-cancerous lesions. It provides a measure of the model's overall diagnostic accuracy.","Perplexity Score":0.95,"ImageBase64":""}}